## Important Notes

- Credit bureaus must respond within 30 days (or 45 days in some circumstances)
- If they don't respond or the response is unsatisfactory, you may have legal options
- Keep all documentation for at least 7 years
- Consider consulting with a consumer rights attorney if your dispute is denied

